ur, Johann Baptist Metz, William Dean, Stanley Hauerwas, Franklin Gamwell, and Ronald Thiemann that can both contribute to and challenge a narrative public theology. She also proposes a model of public theology using narratives from Abraham Lincoln, Virgil Elizondo, and Delores Williams.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aChurch and statezUnited States. 4aPhilosophy : Ethics. 4aReligion and Spirituality : American Religion. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Theology. 7aRELIGION / Theology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780791484371?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791484371423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791484371/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles